net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator

Class Hypervolume

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.Indicator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.UnaryIndicator
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator.Hypervolume
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class Hypervolume
extends UnaryIndicator
    The Hypervolume (HV) obtains the hyper-area covered by a given Pareto front. It requires a maximization problem, as well as objective values in the range [0,1].

    The original implementation in C by Zitzler is available at: ftp://ftp.tik.ee.ethz.ch/pub/people/zitzler/hypervol.c

    Book: C.A. Coello Coello, D.A. Van Veldhuizen, G.B. Lamont. "Evolutionary Algorithms for Solving Multi-Objective Problems". 1st edition. Kluwer Academic Publ. 2002.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
